        "timestamp": "2018-03-20 17:59:50.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n(3 comments)\n\nCould rename \"c\" variables in one of the test files.  Also, the code style guidelines imply that \"<p/>\" is not needed in javadoc comments, and can simply be replaced by an extra blank line.  If true, can remove them",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "8bd5040104c89ed908f95a957e43644207b8ad9d",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 811,
          "name": "Jim Hahn",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-20 18:25:11.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> (3 comments)\n > \n > Could rename \"c\" variables in one of the test files.  Also, the\n > code style guidelines imply that \"<p/>\" is not needed in javadoc\n > comments, and can simply be replaced by an extra blank line.  If\n > true, can remove them\n\nLooks like using blank lines instead of \"<p/>\" does not work.  That being the case, it would probably be better not to merge lines with the lines that contain \"<p/>\", as it makes it more difficult to read the comments when not using javadoc processing.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
